1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:34,270 --> 00:01:41,600
Not Here

3
00:01:41,620 --> 00:01:45,000
Treasure
Repository

4
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:47,840
What a cute creature you are!

5
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:52,670
You're a skeleton from tip to toe,
and yet somehow you're still alive.

6
00:01:52,670 --> 00:01:56,130
You put up a pretty good fight, Soul King.

7
00:01:56,130 --> 00:02:01,600
The Chess Peacekeepers are
totally afraid of you.

8
00:02:03,610 --> 00:02:09,260
There's a reason you're called "Soul King;"
you're basically their nemesis.

9
00:02:09,260 --> 00:02:10,560
But,

10
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:14,820
you were unable to defeat these guys.

11
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:12,740
Napoleon, a Bicorne Hat

12
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,820
Zeus, a Storm Cloud

13
00:02:14,890 --> 00:02:16,690
Prometheus, a Sun

14
00:02:16,690 --> 00:02:21,630
I gave them my soul, so they're a part of me.

15
00:02:22,780 --> 00:02:25,960
That means their souls are in a different class.

16
00:02:32,290 --> 00:02:35,000
We finished our inspection, Mama!

17
00:02:36,020 --> 00:02:39,900
He isn't hiding anything in his clothes!

18
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:44,850
And he doesn't have anything in this tube!

19
00:02:44,850 --> 00:02:46,810
Nor in his cane sword...

20
00:02:46,810 --> 00:02:48,190
And not within his cloak.

21
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:49,880
He has nothing!

22
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:54,320
He didn't steal anything!

23
00:02:56,960 --> 00:03:00,320
That's good to hear, Soul King.

24
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:03,360
I'm sorry that I suspected you. Pet, pet.

25
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:08,120
How frustrating. This is so humiliating.

26
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:11,130
The Tamate Box is one thing,

27
00:03:11,130 --> 00:03:14,730
but I wouldn't be able to let you get away with stealing my poneglyphs, either.

28
00:03:14,730 --> 00:03:18,920
Nor any of the other belongings I have.

29
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:25,600
It'd be foolish if I allowed another person
to take them and reach Laugh Tale again.

30
00:03:30,390 --> 00:03:34,730
I won't make the same mistake that I did with Roger!

31
00:03:34,730 --> 00:03:41,280
He used that strange ability to hear the Voice of All Things and read the stone.

32
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:46,990
But now I've got someone
capable of using a similar ability.

33
00:03:51,660 --> 00:03:57,630
The next to reach Laugh Tale... will be us!

34
00:03:57,630 --> 00:03:58,750
Mama!

35
00:04:00,340 --> 00:04:05,060
Oh, my dear Pudding!
I was just talking about you.

36
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:10,640
What's up?
Has your third eye finally revealed its power?

37
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:14,690
Come on, Mama!
You ask me that every time you see me!

38
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:16,940
I'm a half-blood, remember?

39
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:20,480
There's no guarantee
that I'll ever be able to use that ability.

40
00:04:23,210 --> 00:04:25,290
I'm sorry.

41
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:31,100
But you do have the blood
of the three-eye people in your veins.

42
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:34,340
If you don't awaken
your latent ability as a three-eye,

43
00:04:34,340 --> 00:04:37,170
you'll be nothing but a creepy girl.

44
00:04:42,670 --> 00:04:45,330
P-Pudding-san...

45
00:04:45,330 --> 00:04:46,970
has three eyes?

46
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:50,810
No!

47
00:04:50,810 --> 00:04:53,230
The fact that we know each other...

48
00:04:53,230 --> 00:04:55,690
must be kept secret!

49
00:04:55,690 --> 00:04:58,230
That's that skeleton man.

50
00:04:58,230 --> 00:05:03,710
I didn't expect to see him here.
Well, at least they caught him.

51
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:08,980
Um, Mama? I don't feel comfortable talking
to you in here. Can we go to your room?

52
00:05:08,980 --> 00:05:12,990
Ah, of course! Anything for you.

53
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:48,490
Cock-a-doodle-doo!

54
00:05:50,140 --> 00:05:52,120
That call is...

55
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:55,910
He's about to evolve into his third form!

56
00:05:55,910 --> 00:05:58,290
He's turning into Count Niwatori!

57
00:05:58,860 --> 00:06:00,380
This is stupid.

58
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:03,130
I'll finish him off now.

59
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:06,920
Stop!

60
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:11,500
First was Baron Tamago; then Viscount Hiyoko;
and now it's Count Niwatori!
Note:
Tamago (Egg) – Hiyoko (Chick) – Niwatori (Chicken)

61
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,940
The more he transforms,
the more powerful he gets!

62
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:16,290
He ate the Egg-Egg Fruit!

63
00:06:16,290 --> 00:06:20,560
Count Niwatori is a true knight!
You should be terrified!

64
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:24,600
Once he transforms fully,
he'll have power that you'll be no match for!

65
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:27,030
Stop him from disrupting the transformation!

66
00:06:27,030 --> 00:06:28,650
I'm not going to just sit around and watch.

67
00:06:28,650 --> 00:06:31,950
Stop!

68
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:44,130
Fine, I'll stop.

69
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:46,580
This is it.

70
00:06:59,310 --> 00:07:02,050
It's nice to have so many soldiers around.

71
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:06,780
You bastard! What are you doing?!

72
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,360
Pull back!

73
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,980
Run away!

74
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:19,480
A decoy couldn't ask for more.

75
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,080
Don't do it!

76
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:35,350
Cock-a-doodle-doo!

77
00:07:56,190 --> 00:08:00,100
Mirro-world

78
00:08:03,830 --> 00:08:09,000
Oh, that was close!
You could've been killed, Pedro!

79
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,590
You're so reckless!

80
00:08:11,590 --> 00:08:15,140
Pedro, you really startled me there.

81
00:08:16,090 --> 00:08:18,970
You startled me more.

82
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:22,270
Hey, Pedro!

83
00:08:22,810 --> 00:08:26,730
Imagine if you were in my position, and a mirror spoke to you.

84
00:08:26,730 --> 00:08:30,200
But you managed to come up with a plan
without a second thought!

85
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:32,070
It's just what I expected from you, Pedro!

86
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:35,790
In any case, we're inside of the mirrors?

87
00:08:35,790 --> 00:08:38,080
This is pretty outlandish.

88
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:43,170
No one can come in or get out of here
without Brûlée. We'll be safe here!

89
00:08:43,170 --> 00:08:46,790
If we find Sanji,
we can escape through here with him!

90
00:08:46,790 --> 00:08:49,800
Tell us what you've learned!

91
00:08:52,420 --> 00:08:53,900
What?!

92
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:56,380
Luffy and Nami got caught?!

93
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:58,800
Yeah, that's what I heard.

94
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,580
I'm worried about Brook too.

95
00:09:00,580 --> 00:09:03,770
Let's hope he managed to get a copy of that poneglyph.

96
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:07,230
They're all in danger! Let's hurry up!

97
00:09:07,230 --> 00:09:10,630
Carrot! Did you finish drawing everyone's portrait?

98
00:09:10,630 --> 00:09:12,970
Yes I did, Chobro!

99
00:09:12,970 --> 00:09:15,600
You did?! Good job!

100
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:19,020
Then, let's show the portraits to the mirrors in order to get their locations.

101
00:09:19,020 --> 00:09:20,160
Okay!

102
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:26,200
Mirror, mirror!
Tell us where these people are!

103
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,130
They look nothing like them!

104
00:09:28,130 --> 00:09:32,240
That girl with the long hair just ran past me!

105
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,130
The mirror talked!

106
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:39,300
What? So, did Nami break out? 
Is she with Luffy?

107
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:41,720
She was with Boss Jinbe!

108
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:44,770
J... Jinbe?

109
00:09:44,770 --> 00:09:47,600
W-W-What?!

110
00:09:49,770 --> 00:09:51,650
Sanji!

111
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,670
Third Floor
Midbaum

112
00:09:51,650 --> 00:09:54,150
Answer me if you're here!

113
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:56,360
Stop, Straw Hat!

114
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:58,450
Sanji!

115
00:09:58,450 --> 00:09:59,820
Hey!

116
00:09:59,820 --> 00:10:04,460
I've got something to tell you!
Where are you?!

117
00:10:04,460 --> 00:10:07,620
You gotta hear me out!

118
00:10:09,330 --> 00:10:11,710
Ow, ow, ow...

119
00:10:17,390 --> 00:10:19,550
Where did Straw Hat go?

120
00:10:19,550 --> 00:10:23,090
He's too fast! Which way did he go?

121
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:24,680
Did he go in here?

122
00:10:31,860 --> 00:10:33,350
The door won't open!

123
00:10:33,350 --> 00:10:36,110
Let's go that way!

124
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:36,110
Yeah!

125
00:10:40,410 --> 00:10:43,370
You're... Sanji's sister!

126
00:10:43,370 --> 00:10:44,360
That's correct.

127
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:47,580
What do you want? I'm in a hurry here!

128
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:52,500
You're looking for Sanji, aren't you?
You just missed him.

129
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:55,880
What? Really?!
Where'd he go?!

130
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:59,220
Pudding lied to us!

131
00:10:59,220 --> 00:11:03,980
Pudding—who Sanji thinks he's marrying—
told me that she's gonna kill him!

132
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:08,770
Are you okay? Did you get hurt?

133
00:11:10,230 --> 00:11:13,270
Thanks for asking. I'm fine.

134
00:11:13,270 --> 00:11:16,570
In any case, my brother
already knows about Pudding.

135
00:11:16,570 --> 00:11:20,030
What?! Has he known the whole time?!

136
00:11:20,620 --> 00:11:22,990
He just found out about her.

137
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:28,830
I tried to convince him to escape from this island,

138
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:32,250
but he was worried about the hostages in the East Blue...

139
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:35,540
and your crew as well.

140
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:37,880
Hostages? Do you mean the people at the Baratie?

141
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:44,430
I know them too. If they're really in any danger,
I'll go back to the East Blue and fight to protect them!

142
00:11:47,390 --> 00:11:49,310
Do you want to eat something?

143
00:11:49,310 --> 00:11:51,060
N-No, I'll be fine!

144
00:11:58,020 --> 00:12:00,940
I'll be here waiting!

145
00:12:00,940 --> 00:12:05,790
If you don't come back, I'll be here...

146
00:12:05,790 --> 00:12:08,410
starving to death!

147
00:12:08,410 --> 00:12:12,460
You're the cook of my ship!

148
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:18,710
I won't eat anything other than what you cook!

149
00:12:24,740 --> 00:12:29,100
But... this is good.

150
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:33,050
Sanji knows about Pudding.

151
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:39,250
As long as he's not being tricked, I'm happy.

152
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:42,690
I've done everything else I can!

153
00:12:43,490 --> 00:12:46,410
Okay, thank you, Sanji's sister!

154
00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:49,740
What? Why are you going that way?!

155
00:12:49,740 --> 00:12:54,080
This isn't where I promised to meet him!

156
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:09,050
Sanji!

157
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:17,150
...want us to chop his head off.

158
00:13:19,730 --> 00:13:23,440
You are a sacrifice, Sanji.

159
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:32,740
As long as you don't try to run away,
everything will work out just fine, Sanji.

160
00:13:35,370 --> 00:13:37,830
At the wedding tomorrow...

161
00:13:37,830 --> 00:13:40,290
the entire Vinsmoke family...

162
00:13:42,050 --> 00:13:44,510
will be executed!

163
00:13:49,850 --> 00:13:53,100
Begone from my sight, 
you miserable, lowlife pirate!

164
00:14:00,490 --> 00:14:05,150
It's too late for me to turn back, Luffy.

165
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:15,550
Oh! Something hit my house!

166
00:14:17,370 --> 00:14:19,670
My house!

167
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:21,750
What's going on? It's so late.

168
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:24,670
Is that a person?

169
00:14:35,350 --> 00:14:38,240
H-Hey! Are you okay?

170
00:14:53,410 --> 00:14:55,990
We found you.

171
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:04,660
I gotta get there as soon as possible.

172
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:08,070
I'll be here waiting!

173
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:21,600
I've gotta be waiting...

174
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:24,680
at that spot!

175
00:15:36,210 --> 00:15:37,910
Block off the exits!

176
00:15:43,540 --> 00:15:47,260
Oh, no! We're about to be surrounded.

177
00:15:47,260 --> 00:15:49,920
What? Isn't there a way out?

178
00:15:51,170 --> 00:15:53,010
Can you handle the rear, Nami?

179
00:15:53,010 --> 00:15:56,390
You can count on me!
I'm getting tired of this.

180
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,940
There they are!

181
00:16:01,940 --> 00:16:04,020
Stop!

182
00:16:04,020 --> 00:16:04,730
Nami!

183
00:16:04,730 --> 00:16:06,440
You guys are annoying!

184
00:16:07,220 --> 00:16:08,860
Thundercloud Rod!

185
00:16:24,170 --> 00:16:26,580
What?! Chopper!

186
00:16:26,580 --> 00:16:28,750
What?

187
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:31,730
Chopper! Why are you here?!

188
00:16:31,730 --> 00:16:34,220
Oh! Chobro!

189
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:35,510
Carrot!

190
00:16:35,510 --> 00:16:39,140
Nami! We're here to save you!

191
00:16:39,140 --> 00:16:42,480
I see! I'm so sorry!

192
00:16:43,450 --> 00:16:46,560
Oh, no!
There are more enemies up ahead.

193
00:16:47,450 --> 00:16:50,400
Nami! Get in the mirror now!

194
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,320
What?

195
00:16:55,110 --> 00:16:56,780
Oh, ow, ow!

196
00:16:56,780 --> 00:16:59,210
What's the matter, Prometheus?

197
00:16:56,940 --> 00:17:01,950
Queen's Chamber
Whole Cake Chateau

198
00:16:59,210 --> 00:17:03,340
The wound I got from Soul King is deeper than I thought,

199
00:17:03,340 --> 00:17:05,560
and now it's starting to hurt again!

200
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:07,750
How pathetic!

201
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:11,050
I mean, we should give him some credit.

202
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:16,050
Because no one's ever been able to hurt you guys before.

203
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:22,380
Mama, are you really going to keep holding onto that skeleton?

204
00:17:22,380 --> 00:17:27,680
What? "That skeleton"?
Pudding-san, how could you refer to me like that?

205
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:30,480
Yeah, of course!

206
00:17:29,770 --> 00:17:30,480
Too close!

207
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:34,360
There's no other creature like this!
It's a work of soul art!

208
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:39,920
I'd rather carry him around for a while
instead of putting him in a book.

209
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:40,870
No...

210
00:17:40,870 --> 00:17:44,720
Good job on tricking the Straw Hats.

211
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:49,430
I never expected them to get
through the Seducing Woods.

212
00:17:49,430 --> 00:17:54,750
But now they're trapped
in a book in the Prisoner Library.

213
00:17:55,670 --> 00:18:00,220
Yeah, I went to see them, too.
It serves them right.

214
00:18:00,220 --> 00:18:02,220
"It serves them right"?

215
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:04,220
Are you gonna kill them?

216
00:18:04,220 --> 00:18:06,320
Yeah, after the wedding ceremony.

217
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:10,950
I sent barmaids over to Germa.

218
00:18:10,950 --> 00:18:14,980
They're probably in a drunken stupor right now
and won't be expecting anything!

219
00:18:14,980 --> 00:18:19,800
Good... But Reiju was investigating me.

220
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:24,160
She's a pretty sharp person.
It's a good thing I took care of her.

221
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:28,370
What? You didn't kill her, right?!

222
00:18:28,370 --> 00:18:32,600
Come on, Mama! Don't you trust me?!
I just shot her leg!

223
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:35,550
I shot her once, and then erased her memories.

224
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:39,090
I can't believe this.

225
00:18:42,550 --> 00:18:47,350
Pudding-san ?
Aren't you a sweet girl?

226
00:18:48,850 --> 00:18:53,200
You need to be careful.
You're my precious bride.

227
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:56,510
It'd be a major problem
if she tried to get revenge.

228
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:59,760
Thank you for your concern, Mama.
But...

229
00:19:01,030 --> 00:19:04,490
thanks to her,
I got to test out this gun.

230
00:19:05,220 --> 00:19:11,620
With this gun, even Germa's modified bodies
won't stand a chance.

231
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:16,340
That's great, very great.

232
00:19:16,340 --> 00:19:19,340
You're such a smart girl.

233
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:26,180
When you open fire tomorrow,
that'll be the signal for our plan to begin.

234
00:19:26,180 --> 00:19:29,080
I can't wait.

235
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:33,030
Everyone will be watching
when it's time for the wedding kiss.

236
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:39,780
That dopey-faced Sanji will lift
your veil and try to kiss you.

237
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:41,990
That's when...

238
00:19:41,990 --> 00:19:46,870
he'll see your third eye for the first time!

239
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:58,250
In that moment, he'll see his beautiful bride's creepy face,

240
00:19:59,380 --> 00:20:02,340
and he'll be distracted for a moment!

241
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:06,760
That'll be your cue, okay?
You'll have to finish him off with one shot.

242
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:10,600
Aim right between his eyes!
Right here.

243
00:20:16,430 --> 00:20:20,410
Pudding-san is going to kill Sanji-san ?!

244
00:20:20,410 --> 00:20:24,160
Everyone will be in shock, unable to move.

245
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:29,700
The people of Germa will realize
they're in danger and try to run,

246
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:32,750
but it'll already be too late at that point!

247
00:20:32,750 --> 00:20:38,310
As the unarmed Vinsmokes turn around to run,
they'll notice a wall of guns pointing at them!

248
00:20:41,090 --> 00:20:45,700
They won't even have time
to show fear before their blood spills.

249
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:48,510
Gunshots will be going off like fireworks!

250
00:20:48,510 --> 00:20:52,930
A rain of bullets will continue to pierce their bodies,
even long after they die!

251
00:20:52,930 --> 00:20:55,940
There'll be a giant pool of blood
spreading on the ground!

252
00:20:55,940 --> 00:21:00,110
The six Vinsmokes will be nothing
but mutiliated corpses!

253
00:21:00,110 --> 00:21:03,610
The gunshots will be shots of joy!

254
00:21:03,610 --> 00:21:06,660
And that's when the real party begins!

255
00:21:06,660 --> 00:21:11,190
We'll celebrate with the cake.
We'll toast with tea!

256
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:15,460
Once they lose their useless leader,

257
00:21:16,370 --> 00:21:22,200
all of Germa will belong to me!

258
00:21:24,340 --> 00:21:26,800
Mirro-world

259
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,840
Are you okay, Chobro?

260
00:21:29,470 --> 00:21:33,340
I can't believe it!
We're inside the mirror?!

261
00:21:33,340 --> 00:21:37,740
Jinbe! Why are you with these rats?!

262
00:21:37,740 --> 00:21:39,110
Brûlée.

263
00:21:39,110 --> 00:21:42,360
This is obviously treason.

264
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:49,910
I heard you tried to leave our crew,
but when faced with the roulette, you cowered in fear!

265
00:21:52,290 --> 00:21:57,660
I wanted to repay Mama for protecting
Fishman Island after Whitebeard's death.

266
00:21:57,660 --> 00:22:01,840
Since I wanted to leave,
I wanted to do so honorably for her sake.

267
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:06,760
But I could only sense
death and malice from that roulette.

268
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:09,140
A roulette?

269
00:22:09,140 --> 00:22:13,730
You made the correct choice
not to spin it, Jinbe, Knight of the Sea.

270
00:22:14,270 --> 00:22:22,070
Five years ago, my partner turned that roulette wheel
and asked Big Mom for mercy,

271
00:22:22,070 --> 00:22:24,590
but he lost his life instead.

272
00:22:25,390 --> 00:22:31,050
Those that spin that thing are guaranteed to die.
It was made that way.

273
00:22:31,050 --> 00:22:33,200
So it's rigged?!

274
00:22:35,410 --> 00:22:40,420
Of course it is, you fools!
Mama would never let anyone leave alive!

275
00:22:40,420 --> 00:22:43,170
Whether it's a minor intruder

276
00:22:43,170 --> 00:22:47,670
or an affiliated pirate
who was once loyal!

277
00:22:47,670 --> 00:22:50,340
She welcomes all who come to this land

278
00:22:50,340 --> 00:22:53,340
and kills those who leave!

279
00:22:53,340 --> 00:22:54,650
That's Mama's–

280
00:22:54,650 --> 00:22:56,060
We don't have time for this!

281
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:03,920
Let's keep moving!
We need to find Brook, Luffy, and Sanji!

282
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:07,320
I'm not moving again!
There's too many of you!

283
00:23:07,940 --> 00:23:13,200
Sanji's Room

284
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:26,600
That's right. Prince Sanji, the groom,
is fast asleep in his room.

285
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:32,700
Don't let him out or let anyone in until morning.
Keep a close eye on that door.

286
00:23:32,700 --> 00:23:33,790
Yes, ma'am!

287
00:23:39,390 --> 00:23:44,020
Oh, no! I fell asleep-nasu !
In Prince Sanji's bed!

288
00:23:44,020 --> 00:23:47,280
Is he not back yet-nasu ?

289
00:23:48,570 --> 00:23:51,990
I guess he won't come back
any time soon-nasu.

290
00:23:51,990 --> 00:23:55,450
Well, I might as well sleep a little more-nasu.

291
00:23:55,460 --> 00:23:56,790
In other words,

292
00:23:55,650 --> 00:24:01,850
Meeting Room

293
00:23:56,790 --> 00:23:59,920
Pekoms was with them up until Choclat Town.

294
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:03,120
They're trying to get Sanji back.

295
00:24:03,140 --> 00:24:06,340
There were six of them when Pudding
lured them to the main island.

296
00:24:08,300 --> 00:24:12,380
Mama has Soul King now.

297
00:24:12,380 --> 00:24:13,710
Don't touch this!

298
00:24:13,710 --> 00:24:17,820
And Pedro was in the courtyard on the third floor
when he blew himself up, right?

299
00:24:17,820 --> 00:24:19,640
Indeed-cock-a-doo.

300
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,650
That's two taken care of.

301
00:24:21,650 --> 00:24:26,680
And of the four who entered the Seducing Woods...
the rabbit and raccoon dog...

302
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:31,440
were caught by Big Sis Brûlée.
She informed us of this earlier today.

303
00:24:32,320 --> 00:24:37,160
That means we've taken care of four of the six.
That leaves...

304
00:24:39,410 --> 00:24:44,980
the two who defeated Big Brother Cracker
and escaped from the Seducing Woods.

305
00:24:44,980 --> 00:24:50,340
They were definitely imprisoned
in the underground Prisoner Library.

306
00:24:52,340 --> 00:24:56,010
So why are we getting reports
that they escaped?

307
00:25:05,750 --> 00:25:09,400
Only one of us was there
in the Prisoner Library.

308
00:25:09,740 --> 00:25:15,600
What happened, Big Brother Opera?
What's this about Jinbe showing up?

309
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:19,100
It's a lie!
Don't make me repeat myself!

310
00:25:19,100 --> 00:25:20,600
In fact, where is he now?

311
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:25,160
Nobody has reported a thing!
Nobody came down to the basement!

312
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:31,550
As Mama ordered, I was trying to get
Lola's whereabouts out of them!

313
00:25:31,550 --> 00:25:36,760
They didn't know anything,
so I burned them alive!

314
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:39,550
I know I went a little overboard.

315
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:46,780
D-Don't you trust your older brother, Mont d'Or?!

316
00:25:46,780 --> 00:25:49,230
Of course I do.

317
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:56,560
There's no way I can admit
that I let them get away! Never ever!

318
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:59,870
Mama will take away my lifespan
if she finds out!

319
00:26:02,790 --> 00:26:05,320
What about Sanji and the Vinsmokes?

320
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:07,910
They're in their rooms.

321
00:26:07,910 --> 00:26:09,580
Okay, then everything is fine!

322
00:26:10,590 --> 00:26:13,520
All the intruders have been caught!

323
00:26:13,520 --> 00:26:18,150
Right now, in the great kitchen,
they're preparing the feast for tomorrow!

324
00:26:18,150 --> 00:26:24,570
Let's make tomorrow the greatest wedding ever
for our precious little sister, Pudding!

325
00:26:24,570 --> 00:26:28,390
Yeah!

326
00:26:38,490 --> 00:26:41,310
Cover more ground and continue
to patrol through the night.

327
00:26:41,310 --> 00:26:42,200
Yes, sir!

328
00:26:43,410 --> 00:26:45,830
I can't trust Opera on this one.

329
00:26:46,750 --> 00:26:49,920
Medical Room
Third Floor

330
00:26:52,950 --> 00:26:57,360
Sweet City

331
00:26:57,380 --> 00:26:59,630
In the Chateau

332
00:27:01,050 --> 00:27:04,720
My goodness...
Did I make this for Pudding-chan ?

333
00:27:05,580 --> 00:27:08,100
What was I thinking?

334
00:27:20,430 --> 00:27:23,910
I made their favorite foods.

335
00:27:26,890 --> 00:27:30,180
Forget them! Forget them!

336
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:45,120
I don't need to worry about Luffy and the others.
They can escape on their own.

337
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:49,890
The evil army of Vinsmokes will die,
and so will I.

338
00:27:49,890 --> 00:27:52,310
It'll all go according to Big Mom's plan.

339
00:27:52,310 --> 00:27:54,750
This is for the best.

340
00:27:54,750 --> 00:27:56,970
Our enemies will be satisfied
by getting what they want.

341
00:27:56,970 --> 00:28:01,400
It's been short, but I've had a fulfilling life.

342
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:04,680
Oh, food!

343
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:10,160
Aren't you Vinsmoke Sanji?

344
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:13,330
Mont d'Or said you were
sleeping in your room.

345
00:28:14,580 --> 00:28:19,180
If you don't come back, I'll be here...

346
00:28:19,180 --> 00:28:21,800
starving to death!

347
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:24,550
Don't touch that!

348
00:28:25,390 --> 00:28:27,350
That meat there...

349
00:28:30,620 --> 00:28:31,960
doesn't belong to you!

350
00:28:43,180 --> 00:28:45,150
I heard a loud noise down the hall!

351
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:53,110
You son of a...

352
00:28:57,880 --> 00:29:00,340
Hey, stop, you bastard!

353
00:29:05,470 --> 00:29:07,330
What the hell am I doing?
